    <description>The MIRO instrument consisted of two heterodyne radiometers at two wavelengths: 1.3mm with a continuum bandwidth of 0.5 GHz; and 0.5 mm with a continuum bandwidth of 1.0 GHz. The submillimeter receiver had a total spectroscopic bandwidth of 180 MHz, and spectral resolution of 44 kHz. In spectroscopic mode, MIRO could observe 4096 channels (bandwidth 44kHz) simultaneously.</description>
